values: UCLA, USC, and Reitaku University join forces to host the 6th Annual Humanitarian Mapathon, a free mapping competition to support the Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team (HOT). Everybody is welcome to attend, whether you have any mapping experience or not! Training will be provided to ensure that you are able to participate and contribute to humanitarian causes around the world.
This three-day international hybrid event will include student speakers, hands-on training, donuts, prizes, and more. Join a community of humanitarian mappers, and let's all make a difference.
Register and get the mapathon Zoom link.
The mapathon will span a two-day period starting at _____ to _____. Check out the full agenda here.
New to OpenStreetMap and humanitarian mapping? We got you covered! Follow this step-by-step tutorial and you'll be mapping in just a few minutes.
For the duration of the two-day mapathon, our Slack channel will be monitored by the friendly mapathon experts. Join the channel to say "Hi", meet other mapathoners, and ask us questions.
Note that the leaderboard may take time (sometimes a few hours) to reflect the most recent changes.
